# iOS / Capacitor workflow

This repo is a React+Vite PWA **and** a Capacitor iOS app. The web/Vercel build is
unchanged; Capacitor adds `capacitor.config.ts` and the `ios/` Xcode project
(committed to git). Full plan and future backlog: `docs/capacitor-ios-plan.md`.

## Facts

- App name: **Bourdon**, bundle ID: **`com.margokolar.bourdon`**, web dir: `dist`
- Capacitor 8, iOS platform uses **SPM** (no CocoaPods)
- `xcode-select` points to CommandLineTools on this Mac; always set
  `DEVELOPER_DIR=/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer` for `xcodebuild`/`xcrun`
  (the deploy script does this itself)
- Signing: **free Apple ID (Personal Team)** for now — installs expire after 7 days;
  re-running the deploy refreshes them. No Apple Developer Program yet, so no
  TestFlight and no `xcodebuild archive` for distribution.
- The signing team was selected manually in Xcode once; do not change signing
  settings in `project.pbxproj` without being asked.

## Commands

- `npm run ios` — full deploy: web build → `cap sync ios` → `xcodebuild` → install +
  launch on the connected iPhone (`scripts/ios-deploy.sh`). Phone must be plugged in
  (or Wi-Fi paired) and unlocked. If no phone is reachable, the script builds the
  app anyway and skips the install (exit 0).
- `npm run ios:sync` — web build + `cap sync ios` only (after web-code changes)
- `npm run ios:open` — open the Xcode project (rarely needed)
- After changing anything under `ios/` native config or adding Capacitor plugins,
  run `npx cap sync ios`.

## Rules

- Web-only changes still get verified with `npm run dev` / `npm run build`; only
  deploy to the phone when the user wants to test on the phone.
- Do not add native plugins, MIDI, or live-audio work unless the user asks — that is
  future backlog (Phases 2–5 in the plan doc).
- Never commit `ios/App/App/public` or `ios/DerivedData` (already gitignored).
- The user (Margo) is non-technical: he should never need to open Xcode. If a deploy
  fails, diagnose and fix it via CLI; explain in plain Estonian what he must do on
  the phone (e.g. trust dialogs), if anything.
